translated: Örn, Carl Henrik Gunnar, senior physician, general practitioner, doctor, Linköping, born on 30/10/06 in Karlstad to district physician Elis Ö. and Thérèse Uggla. Married in 1942 to Sif Ahrén. Children: Claes Henrik, born in 1943, and Eva, born in 1945. Completed high school in Linköping in 1925, obtained a Bachelor's degree in medicine in 1929, and a medical licentiate in Stockholm in 1934. In his career, he held various short-term positions as well as assistant physician at Linköping State Hospital's medical department from 1934 to 1940, at Orup's Psychiatric Hospital in 1936-1937, at the Epidemic Hospital in Stockholm from 1941 to 1944, and at the Children's Hospital Samariten in 1944. Served as a naval doctor on the Fik cruise from 1937, with military appointments from 1937 to 1944. Chief physician at the Central Epidemic Hospital in Linköping from 1945. Also had periods of study abroad in 1938 and 1946.
